<concept id="concept_13713685F7764833A6ECE39580167502">
  <title>Conditional Execution using Firing Rules</title>
  <shortdesc>Tags defined in custom code tags can be fired conditionally based
	 on matching criteria. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Developer and implementation" />
      <othermeta name="subtopic" content="Tag management" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody>
    <p>All conditions that you define for a custom code tag must be met for the
		code to execute. For example, if you provide a Host Match and Path Match, both
		conditions must match. 
	 </p>
    <p>The following match parameters are available:
	 </p>
    <ul id="ul_66F8457A4A354C56ADEE0050D6FCBB21">
      <li id="li_BC8ADC881489401B82FC22375D8EFEBE">Host
		</li>
      <li id="li_C83DC00698504D3E9C01AAFEB239E1AE">Path
		</li>
      <li id="li_0B4BA42C2E3B4A6C9253D7D7271F5BC5">Cookie
		</li>
      <li id="li_097969956BCC419C8087AEF08AB0B339">Query Parameter
		</li>
      <li id="li_86C9FCD5C8964763B82F055E917E3960">Date
		</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The following match conditions are available:
	 </p>
    <ul id="ul_17324EA6493347A58B96EF164FC7E692">
      <li id="li_3D80409FC07744F5BE3FDE876ED12BA2">Contains
		</li>
      <li id="li_047C86B34B8A4A2D9D85D66F09E6E738">Matches RegEx
		</li>
      <li id="li_695049B862B94A56A9E2A23CCB2BD199">Does not contain
		</li>
      <li id="li_EC76C3E9779842F6955F21A080C68746">Does not match RegEx
		</li>
    </ul>
    <p>RegEx conditions use standard JavaScript 
		<xref href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/JavaScript/Guide/Regular_Expressions" format="https" scope="external">RegEx patterns</xref>.
	 </p>
    <p>Match strings in contains and does not contain conditions are
		case-sensitive. 
	 </p>
  </conbody>
</concept>